        "Austin Hayes is currently a sophomore attending Colegio Episcopal de Panamá. Austin has been an active member in the debate club since 8th grade. This will be his first time being chair at CEPMOAS and he is very pleased to be moderator of the World Humanitarian Summit. Originally from Chicago, Austin has excelled at a number of national and international debate conferences such as CEPMOAS, National Congress for Excellence, PANAMUN, and HACIA Democracy. His enormous dedication to debate has made him stand out both as a delegate and now as a chair. His main recommendations for delegates is to prepare well and to immerse themselves in the humanitarian situation occurring in Syria."
