    permanent:
      title: "Permanent Council of the OAS"
      topic: "Money Laundering and Tax Havens in the American Continent"
      topicBio: [
        "The American continent has battled against money laundering and tax havens for decades. Both issues continue to harm emerging economies since they allow criminals to fund their illegal activities. Money laundering occurs when illegally obtained funds are used in the legitimate financial system. A tax haven is a country or territory that has minimal tax controls, especially over foreign-based corporations."
        "Numerous efforts by governments and NGOs have been made to diminish the influence of money laundering and tax havens, but continued corruption and drug trafficking strongly reduces the impact of these measures. Corruption means politicians do little to nothing to really fight money laundering. Drug trafficking means there is a potent risk of death for those that dare to combat money laundering. However, this does not mean there cannot be fresh ideas for addressing this issue."
      ]
      chairsBio: [
        "Luigi Iovane is one of the co-chairs of the Permanent Council of the OAS. He’s currently a senior at CEP and he joined the debate club in 2011, when he was in eighth grade. He chaired his first committee in 2013 (Crisis Cabinet), and this will be his third time chairing a committee in CEP MOAS. During his time in the club, Luigi has participated in numerous conferences and has won a considerable number of awards, and this year he was elected president of the debate club. He likes political topics, especially those related to Panama, and he enjoys going to Crisis Cabinets, but he occasionally debates in Asamblea."
        "Alexis Feuillet is a junior at Colegio Episcopal de Panamá. This will be his fourth CEP MOAS and his first time chairing at our conference. Debate has become a huge part of his life since he joined the school's club, and it has taught him a lot about hard work and responsibility.  He is really excited to meet you and see you all debate. Alexis is very certain that every delegate's participation will make this debate unforgettable and he knows that this year's conference is going to be as excellent and thrilling as ever. He wishes you all an amazing time!"
      ]
