    crisis:
      title: "Crisis Cabinet"
      topic: "Jimmy Carter's Executive Cabinet: 1979 Iranian Hostage Crisis"
      topicBio: [
        "On the fourth of November 1979, the Embassy of the United States in Tehran, Iran, was overrun by members of an extremist student group. During that raid, 63 of the 66 Americans present in the embassy were taken hostage. Three Americans were able to flee the compound and take refuge in the Swiss Embassy. However, three other Americans were seized at the Iranian Foreign Ministry bringing the total number of hostages back to 66."
        "As a result, the Executive Cabinet of President Carter has been summoned in order to cope with this situation that has defined the policy of the United States towards the Middle East. At the time of this crisis, all 66 Americans’ lives are now in the hands of the Commander in Chief and his most trusted advisors."
      ]
